3
00:00:11,779 --> 00:00:14,896
This story stared
many thousands of years ago...

4
00:00:14,939 --> 00:00:18,136
but it was all over
in just seven days.

5
00:00:18,179 --> 00:00:20,056
All that long, long time ago...

6
00:00:20,099 --> 00:00:22,135
none of the things
we can see now--

7
00:00:22,179 --> 00:00:25,137
the sun, the moon,
the stars, the earh...

8
00:00:25,179 --> 00:00:28,808
the animals and plants--
not a single one existed.

9
00:00:28,859 --> 00:00:30,736
only god existed...

10
00:00:30,779 --> 00:00:33,293
and so only He
could have created them.

11
00:00:33,339 --> 00:00:34,931
And He did.

12
00:01:57,499 --> 00:01:59,376
[Screaming]

13
00:02:05,379 --> 00:02:06,607
[Sobs]

14
00:02:12,379 --> 00:02:15,530
[Panting]

15
00:02:15,579 --> 00:02:18,013
[gasping]

16
00:02:35,339 --> 00:02:37,250
[Laughter]

17
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:42,292
MRS MILLS : Simpson.
what a character he was.

18
00:02:42,339 --> 00:02:44,489
I wonder
whatever became of him ?

19
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:46,814
MR TUTTLE: oh, I imagine
he 's dead like all the rest.

20
00:02:46,859 --> 00:02:49,373
MRS MILLS :
Ah, those were the days.

21
00:02:52,259 --> 00:02:54,329
[Bell rings]

22
00:02:58,379 --> 00:03:00,290
Mr Tuttle, your hair.

23
00:03:02,219 --> 00:03:04,369
[Lock clicks]

24
00:03:07,939 --> 00:03:09,292
Yes ?

25
00:03:09,339 --> 00:03:12,172
good morning, ma 'am.
we 've come about the--

26
00:03:12,219 --> 00:03:15,609
oh, yes, of course.

27
00:03:15,659 --> 00:03:16,853
Come in.

28
00:03:18,419 --> 00:03:20,455
I wasn 't expecting you so soon.

29
00:03:28,139 --> 00:03:29,413
You are... ?

30
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:30,972
I'm Berha Mills, ma 'am.

31
00:03:31,019 --> 00:03:33,169
And this is Edmund Tuttle.

32
00:03:33,219 --> 00:03:34,811
Pleased to meet you, ma 'am.

33
00:03:34,859 --> 00:03:36,531
You must be the gardener.

34
00:03:36,579 --> 00:03:38,809
That's right. The gardener.

35
00:03:38,859 --> 00:03:42,693
And this young lady
is called Lydia.

36
00:03:42,739 --> 00:03:45,094
Have you had
much experience in service ?

37
00:03:45,139 --> 00:03:48,211
oh, don 't let that angel face
fool you, ma 'am.

38
00:03:48,259 --> 00:03:50,250
She 's older than she looks.

39
00:03:50,299 --> 00:03:52,096
Can you iron ?

40
00:03:54,259 --> 00:03:56,329
what's the matter?
