43
00:04:02,139 --> 00:04:03,572
oh.

44
00:04:03,619 --> 00:04:05,098
oh, but she 's
a good little worker.

45
00:04:05,139 --> 00:04:06,288
I can promise you that.

46
00:04:06,339 --> 00:04:08,773
All right.

47
00:04:08,819 --> 00:04:11,253
All right. The other girl
I had spoke too much, anyway.

48
00:04:11,299 --> 00:04:13,893
Follow me.
Mrs Mills, you and the girl...

49
00:04:13,939 --> 00:04:16,578
will sleep in the attic room
at the top of the stairs.

50
00:04:16,619 --> 00:04:19,850
-And you, Mr...
- Tuttle, ma 'am.

51
00:04:19,899 --> 00:04:24,256
You could sleep in the shed
