61
00:04:47,299 --> 00:04:48,937
Hence my adverisement
in the newspaper...

62
00:04:48,979 --> 00:04:52,289
requesting honest,
hard-working people.

63
00:04:52,339 --> 00:04:54,978
There 's nobody more honest
or hard-working than us.

64
00:04:55,019 --> 00:04:56,293
Isn 't that right, Mr Tuttle ?

65
00:04:56,339 --> 00:04:58,409
oh, aye, we 're very honest.

66
00:04:58,459 --> 00:05:01,451
And, um, very hard-working.

67
00:05:04,219 --> 00:05:06,494
The kitchen.

68
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:08,336
I have breakfast at 8. 00...

69
00:05:08,379 --> 00:05:10,335
the children at 9. 00.

70
00:05:10,379 --> 00:05:13,451
Lunch will be served at 1. 00
and dinner at 7 30.

71
00:05:13,499 --> 00:05:15,729
MRS MILLS :
And the master, ma 'am ?

72
00:05:18,219 --> 00:05:20,608
The master went off to war...

73
00:05:20,659 --> 00:05:22,456
a year and a half ago.

74
00:05:22,499 --> 00:05:26,287
I've had no news
since the war ended.

75
00:05:26,339 --> 00:05:27,738
which of you does the cooking?

76
00:05:27,779 --> 00:05:30,054
MRS MILLS :
I'm so sorry, ma 'am.

77
00:05:30,099 --> 00:05:32,090
which of you does the cooking?

78
00:05:32,139 --> 00:05:33,936
You 'll notice what I'm doing.

79
00:05:33,979 --> 00:05:37,369
In this house,
no door must be opened...

80
00:05:37,419 --> 00:05:39,455
