being closed first.

81
00:05:39,499 --> 00:05:42,059
It is vital
that you remember this.

82
00:05:42,099 --> 00:05:44,055
It's not as easy
as it may seem.

83
00:05:44,099 --> 00:05:47,057
There are 1 5 different keys
for all of the 50 doors...

84
00:05:47,099 --> 00:05:50,375
depending on which area of
the house you 're in at the time.

85
00:05:50,419 --> 00:05:52,887
Mrs Mills,
from tomorrow onwards...

86
00:05:52,939 --> 00:05:55,294
I will be leaving
a set of keys in your charge.

87
00:05:55,339 --> 00:05:56,738
Yes, ma 'am.

88
00:05:56,779 --> 00:05:58,656
The music room.

89
00:05:58,699 --> 00:06:00,929
That old piano was already here
when we moved in.

90
00:06:00,979 --> 00:06:04,938
Please do not let
the children thump away on it.

91
00:06:04,979 --> 00:06:06,617
It sets off my migraine.

92
00:06:06,659 --> 00:06:11,130
Silence is something that we
prize very highly in this house.

93
00:06:11,179 --> 00:06:13,739
That is why you will not find
a telephone, a radio...

94
00:06:13,779 --> 00:06:15,895
or anything else
that makes a racket.

95
00:06:15,939 --> 00:06:18,089
oh, we don 't have
electricity, either.

96
00:06:18,139 --> 00:06:20,369
During the war, the germans
kept cutting it off...

97
00:06:20,419 --> 00:06:22,887
so we learned to live
without it. Let's continue.

98
00:06:22,939 --> 00:06:25,453
Ma 'am, there 's no need
to show us the whole house.

99
00:06:25,499 --> 00:06:26,648
GRACE: Yes!.

100
00:06:26,699 --> 00:06:29,657
Yes, there is.

101
00:06:29,699 --> 00:06:32,213
Most of the time,
you can hardly see your way.

102
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:34,056
It's often difficult
to make out...

103
00:06:34,099 --> 00:06:37,171
if there is a table, a chair,
a door, a sideboard...

104
00:06:37,219 --> 00:06:41,098
or one of my children
playing hide and seek.

105
00:06:41,139 --> 00:06:44,097
what do you mean, ma 'am ?

106
00:06:44,139 --> 00:06:47,051
Perhaps I should introduce you
to the children.

107
00:06:47,139 --> 00:06:48,367
[Lock clicks]

108
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:54,649
Mr Tuttle,
you can see to the garden now.

109
00:06:54,699 --> 00:06:55,893
You 'll find tools in the shed.

110
00:06:55,939 --> 00:06:57,531
Yes, ma 'am.

111
00:06:57,579 --> 00:07:00,013
You two can star closing
the curains.

112
00:07:00,059 --> 00:07:01,651
All of them.

113
00:07:30,499 --> 00:07:32,251
Come.

114
00:07:42,539 --> 00:07:45,815
I'll wake them.
You wait here.

115
00:07:45,859 --> 00:07:48,009
whatever you do,
don 't open the curains.

116
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:53,374
wakey, wakey.

117
00:07:55,579 --> 00:07:57,570
: Now, come on.

118
00:07:57,619 --> 00:08:00,372
Eyes closed, hands together.

119
00:08:00,419 --> 00:08:03,331
CHILDREN:
Let it be, at light of day...

120
00:08:03,379 --> 00:08:05,495
Jesus, to whom now I pray.

121
00:08:05,539 --> 00:08:07,814
Blessed be the Virgin pure...

122
00:08:07,859 --> 00:08:09,850
whom I greet with faith
too shor.

123
00:08:09,899 --> 00:08:11,969
Jesus, Mary, spotless rose...

124
00:08:12,019 --> 00:08:15,136
keep us till this day
doth close.

125
00:08:20,099 --> 00:08:22,374
:
They're still half asleep.

126
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:25,855
MRS MILLS :
what sweet little children.

127
00:08:25,899 --> 00:08:29,096
well... what do you say?

128
00:08:29,139 --> 00:08:31,095
How do you do ?

129
00:08:31,139 --> 00:08:32,970
How do you do ?

130
00:08:33,019 --> 00:08:36,329
How do you do, children ?

131
00:08:36,379 --> 00:08:38,051
My name is Mrs Mills...

132
00:08:38,099 --> 00:08:41,136
but you can call me
Berha if you like.

133
00:08:41,179 --> 00:08:42,931
what are your names ?

134
00:08:42,979 --> 00:08:45,573
-Anne.
-Nicholas.

135
00:08:45,619 --> 00:08:49,817
Anne and Nicholas.
what pretty names.

136
00:08:49,859 --> 00:08:52,612
ANNE: Are you going to be
our new nanny?

137
00:08:52,659 --> 00:08:54,536
Mm-hmm.

138
00:08:55,539 --> 00:08:58,849
Yes, my dears.
I'm your new nanny.

139
00:08:58,899 --> 00:09:00,617
It's time for their breakfast.

140
00:09:00,659 --> 00:09:02,650
Lydia, go to the kitchen
and close every shutter.

141
00:09:02,699 --> 00:09:04,371
[Keys jingle]

142
00:09:09,339 --> 00:09:12,012
The doctors were never able
to find a cure.

143
00:09:12,059 --> 00:09:13,936
For what?

144
00:09:13,979 --> 00:09:16,209
Their condition.

145
00:09:16,259 --> 00:09:20,571
The children have
a very serious allergy to light.

146
00:09:20,619 --> 00:09:22,849
They are photosensitive
and must never be exposed...

147
00:09:22,899 --> 00:09:25,174
