171
00:10:23,419 --> 00:10:25,296
Be quiet!

172
00:10:26,859 --> 00:10:31,489
what do you mean, Anne ?
what happened?

173
00:10:31,539 --> 00:10:35,578
Mummy went... mad.

174
00:10:35,619 --> 00:10:38,292
-Nothing happened.
- Yes, it did.

175
00:10:38,339 --> 00:10:40,216
-No, it didn 't!
- Yes, it did!

176
00:10:40,259 --> 00:10:42,329
GRACE: Be quiet.

177
00:10:44,099 --> 00:10:47,011
what's going on ?
I want those plates empty...

178
00:10:47,059 --> 00:10:49,254
in less than a minute.
Is that clear?

179
00:10:52,419 --> 00:10:54,569
Mrs Mills, would you
come outside a moment?

180
00:10:54,619 --> 00:10:56,575
I'd like a word with you.

181
00:10:58,259 --> 00:10:59,692
Yes, ma 'am.

182
00:11:03,179 --> 00:11:07,218
The postman usually
comes every wednesday.

183
00:11:07,259 --> 00:11:08,658
But I just checked
the letter-box...

184
00:11:08,699 --> 00:11:10,894
and this week he hasn 't.

185
00:11:10,939 --> 00:11:12,850
I'm afraid
I don 't follow, ma 'am.

186
00:11:12,899 --> 00:11:14,730
This letter
should have been collected...

187
00:11:14,779 --> 00:11:17,339
and delivered to
the newspaper five days ago.

188
00:11:17,379 --> 00:11:18,778
It's an adverisement
for servants.

189
00:11:18,819 --> 00:11:20,013
Since it was never published...

190
00:11:20,059 --> 00:11:22,653
would you explain
what you 're doing here ?

191
00:11:22,699 --> 00:11:25,497
oh, I understand.

192
00:11:25,539 --> 00:11:28,497
Ma 'am, that's what
I was going to say to you...

193
00:11:28,539 --> 00:11:29,972
when you opened the door to us.

194
00:11:30,019 --> 00:11:32,408
The truth is
that we just come by...

195
00:11:32,459 --> 00:11:34,654
on the off chance.

196
00:11:34,699 --> 00:11:36,212
A big house like this...

197
00:11:36,259 --> 00:11:38,727
is always in need of someone
who knows the ropes.

198
00:11:38,779 --> 00:11:41,577
You 've served in a house
like this one before ?

199
00:11:41,619 --> 00:11:44,133
This may come as a surprise
to you, ma 'am, but...

200
00:11:44,179 --> 00:11:47,808
we, in fact,
used to work here.

201
00:11:48,979 --> 00:11:50,128
Here ?

202
00:11:50,179 --> 00:11:54,457
oh, now,
'twas a few years ago.

203
00:11:54,499 --> 00:11:57,332
If you don 't mind
my saying so, ma 'am...

204
00:11:57,379 --> 00:12:01,008
they were the best years
of my life.

205
00:12:01,059 --> 00:12:04,256
That's why we come by,
because this house...

206
00:12:04,299 --> 00:12:06,130
means a lot to us.

207
00:12:06,179 --> 00:12:09,012
Perhaps I'd best show you
our references, ma 'am.

208
00:12:09,059 --> 00:12:11,732
No, no, no. Don 't bother.
There 's no need.

209
00:12:11,779 --> 00:12:13,849
So you say
you know the house well?

210
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:16,254
MRS MILLS :
Like the back of my hand.

211
00:12:16,299 --> 00:12:19,291
That is assuming the walls
haven 't sprouted legs...

212
00:12:19,339 --> 00:12:21,250
and moved in the meantime.

213
00:12:21,299 --> 00:12:24,336
GRACE: The only thing
that moves here is the light.

214
00:12:25,779 --> 00:12:28,771
[Sighs]
But it changes everything.

215
00:12:33,259 --> 00:12:35,773
It's rather difficult,
to say the least.

216
00:12:37,059 --> 00:12:41,018
